The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Rain, relief on radar
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Rain, relief on radar
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The weatherman held out hope of rain or thundershowers over the next 24 hours on a Monday that saw the maximum temperature drop by two points to 36.1 degrees Celsius and the minimum dip five points to 24 degrees Celsius.        
	It did not rain much on Monday evening but the conditions are favourable for more rain or thundershowers on Tuesday, said an official of the Regional Meteorological Centre at Alipore.        
	Till 5.30pm, the city had received 12.7mm of rain in 24 hours. Isolated thundersqualls are likely in south Bengal in the next 48 hours, said an official of the India Meteorological Department in Delhi.                                                                                                                                                          
